#Hour of Eternity (#1085, "casting it for 0 extra mana lets you choose a target"):
#cast at X=0 - no targets may be exiled, no token made. The attempted graveyard
#click must do nothing.
[INIT]
firstmain
[PLAYER1]
manapool:{U}{U}{U}
hand:hour of eternity
graveyard:grizzly bears
[PLAYER2]
[DO]
hour of eternity
choice 0
goto firstmain
goto firstmain
grizzly bears
goto firstmain
goto firstmain
[ASSERT]
FIRSTMAIN
[PLAYER1]
graveyard:hour of eternity,grizzly bears
[PLAYER2]
[END]
#PARKED - REAL BUG REPRODUCED + MAPPED (X=0 still exiles a target and makes a token):
#  - <prexx> was parsed by NOTHING (WParsedInt fell to atoi=0); the prexx branch is
#    now added (setX, or pre-cast leftover/2) - kept, semantically correct.
#  - The REAL hole: TargetChooser::addTarget never checks full(), so a maxtargets=0
#    chooser still accepts clicks. Gating addTarget on !full() SEGFAULTS elsewhere
#    (something relies on unconditional adds); gating canTarget(maxtargets==0)
#    makes X=0 casts impossible (castability scans canTarget). The fix needs the
#    targeting-spine round: enforce the cap at add time without breaking the
#    castability scan or whatever dereferences after a refused add.
